Medicine Reminder System
Project Overview

The Medicine Reminder System is a simple Java application designed to remind users to take their medicine at specific scheduled times. The system checks the current time and compares it with predefined medicine timings. When the time matches the schedule, the program alerts the user through a console message and a popup notification.

Features

Checks the current system time automatically

Morning and night medicine reminders

Popup alert when it is time to take medicine

User input to activate reminder (yes/no)

Simple and easy-to-use interface

Technologies Used

Java

Java Time API (LocalTime)

Scanner for user input

JOptionPane for popup notifications

How the Program Works

The program asks the user if they have a migraine condition.

If the user answers yes, the reminder system becomes active.

The program checks the current system time.

If the time falls within the scheduled intervals (morning or night), a reminder message and popup alert are displayed.

If the time does not match the schedule, the program informs the user that no medicine is scheduled at that time.

How to Run the Program

Compile the Java file using:

javac ReminderSystem.java

Run the program using:

java ReminderSystem
Conclusion

This project demonstrates how Java programming can be used to build a simple reminder system that helps users remember their medicine schedule.
